###############################################################################
#
#  Name: index_access_mapping
#
#  Author: Thomas Bayus  (Thomas.Bayus@abbvie.com)
#
#  Version: 1.1.1
#
#  Support: None. Use as-is. No warranties.  
#   
#  Tested: Splunk 7.1.2
#
#  Requires: SANKEY visualization (but will operate without it)
#
#  Deployment: To Search head only, manually, or by deployment server. 
#
#              You can also deploy this to a Splunk Monitoring Console in
#              which case the drop down menu for Search Head will display
#              all of the Search Heads that the MC knows about.
#
#  This app contains nothing funky, just a Table of Contents and a Dashboard 
#  with multilevel left-joining REST API calls.
#
#  This app uses the REST APIs for Indexes, Roles, LDAP_groups, and Users 
#  to knit together a table showing who has access to which directory via 
#  which Roles and LDAP_groups.
#  
#  Output is via a table, and a set of SANKEY diagrams, which show the mappings
#  from index -> role -> LDAP group -> user
#
#  License is: Unlicense = http://unlicense.org
#
###############################################################################
